,\"className\":\"underline hover:text-primary\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"children\":\"kamyu104/LeetCode-Solutions\"}],\". Explanations are original AlgoForge content.\"]}]]}]}]]}]\na:[\"$\",\"$1\",\"c\",{\"children\":[null,[\"$\",\"$L13\",null,{\"parallelRouterKey\":\"children\",\"error\":\"$undefined\",\"errorStyles\":\"$undefined\",\"errorScripts\":\"$undefined\",\"template\":[\"$\",\"$L14\",null,{}],\"templateStyles\":\"$undefined\",\"templateScripts\":\"$undefined\",\"notFound\":\"$undefined\",\"forbidden\":\"$undefined\",\"unauthorized\":\"$undefined\"}]]}]\nb:[\"$\",\"$1\",\"c\",{\"children\":[null,[\"$\",\"$L13\",null,{\"parallelRouterKey\":\"children\",\"error\":\"$undefined\",\"errorStyles\":\"$undefined\",\"errorScripts\":\"$undefined\",\"template\":[\"$\",\"$L14\",null,{}],\"templateStyles\":\"$undefined\",\"templateScripts\":\"$undefined\",\"notFound\":\"$undefined\",\"forbidden\":\"$undefined\",\"unauthorized\":\"$undefined\"}]]}]\nc:[\"$\",\"$1\",\"c\",{\"children\":[null,[\"$\",\"$L13\",null,{\"parallelRouterKey\":\"children\",\"error\":\"$undefined\",\"errorStyles\":\"$undefined\",\"errorScripts\":\"$undefined\",\"template\":[\"$\",\"$L14\",null,{}],\"templateStyles\":\"$undefined\",\"templateScripts\":\"$undefined\",\"notFound\":\"$undefined\",\"forbidden\":\"$undefined\",\"unauthorized\":\"$undefined\"}]]}]\nd:[\"$\",\"$1\",\"c\",{\"children\":[\"$L15\",[[\"$\",\"script\",\"script-0\",{\"src\":\"/_next/static/chunks/0a2gmow1_jiq0.js\",\"async\":true,\"nonce\":\"$undefined\"}]],[\"$\",\"$L16\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$17\",null,{\"name\":\"Next.MetadataOutlet\",\"children\":\"$@18\"}]}]]}]\n19:[]\ne:\"$W19\"\nf:[\"$\",\"$1\",\"h\",{\"children\":[null,[\"$\",\"$L1a\",null,{\"children\":\"$L1b\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"hidden\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L1c\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$17\",null,{\"name\":\"Next.Metadata\",\"children\":\"$L1d\"}]}]}],[\"$\",\"meta\",null,{\"name\":\"next-size-adjust\",\"content\":\"\"}]]}]\n11:[\"$\",\"link\",\"0\",{\"rel\":\"stylesheet\",\"href\":\"/_next/static/chunks/340fxer6uczx7.css\",\"precedence\":\"next\",\"crossOrigin\":\"$undefined\",\"nonce\":\"$undefined\"}]\n1e:I[705747,[\"/_next/static/chunks/2fvm6eoqeukxu.js\",\"/_next/static/chunks/1ntn7efqc-iiw.js\",\"/_next/static/chunks/0plpm2axnqe9k.js\",\"/_next/static/chunks/0a2gmow1_jiq0.js\"],\"CodeTabs\"]\n1f:T356a,// Time:  O(n) on average\n// Space: O(n)\n\n// random algorithms, variant of closest pair\n// reference: https://github.com/jilljenn/tryalgo/blob/master/tryalgo/closest_points.py\nclass Solution {\nprivate:\n    template<typename T>\n    struct VectorHash {\n        size_t operator()(const std::vector<T>& v) const {\n            size_t seed = 0;\n            for (const auto& i : v) {\n                seed ^= std::hash<T>{}(i)  + 0x9e3779b9 + (seed<<6) + (seed>>2);\n            }\n            return seed;\n        }\n    };\n\npublic:\n    vector<int> beautifulPair(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {\n        static const int INF = numeric_limits<int>::max();\n        srand(time(0));\n\n        vector<vector<int>> points;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(nums1); ++i) {\n            points.push_back({nums1[i], nums2[i], i});\n        }\n        vector<int> result(3, INF);\n        unordered_map<vector<int>, int, VectorHash<int>> lookup;\n        for (int i = size(points) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {\n            const auto& key = vector<int>{points[i][0], points[i][1]};\n            if (lookup.count(key)) {\n                result = min(result, vector<int>{0, i, lookup[key]});\n            }\n            lookup[key] = i;\n        }\n        if (result[0] == 0) {\n            return {result[1], result[2]};\n        }\n        vector<int> order(size(points));\n        iota(begin(order), end(order), 0);\n        sort(begin(order), end(order), [&](const auto& a, const auto& b) {\n            return points[a] < points[b];\n        });\n        const auto& dist = [&](auto a, auto b) {\n            if (a[2] > b[2]) {\n                swap(a, b);\n            }\n            return vector<int>{abs(a[0] - b[0]) + abs(a[1] - b[1]), a[2], b[2]};\n        };\n\n        const auto& improve = [&]() {\n            unordered_map<vector<int>, vector<int>, VectorHash<int>> lookup;\n            for (const auto& p : points) {\n                const double size = result[0] / 2.0;\n                const int i = floor(p[0] / size), j = floor(p[1] / size);\n                for (int ni = i - 2; ni <= i + 2; ++ni) {\n                    for (int nj = j - 2; nj <= j + 2; ++nj) {\n                        const auto& key = vector<int>{ni, nj};\n                        if (!lookup.count(key)) {\n                            continue;\n                        }\n                        const auto& d = dist(p, lookup[key]);\n                        if (d < result) {\n                            result = d;\n                            return true;\n                        }\n                    }\n                }\n                lookup[vector<int>{i, j}] = p;\n            }\n            return false;\n        };\n\n        random_shuffle(begin(points), end(points));\n        result = dist(points[0], points[1]);\n        while (improve());\n        return {result[1], result[2]};\n    }\n};\n\n// Time:  O(nlogn)\n// Space: O(n)\n// divide and conquer, merge sort, variant of closest pair\n// reference: https://www.baeldung.com/cs/minimal-manhattan-distance\nclass Solution2 {\nprivate:\n    template<typename T>\n    struct VectorHash {\n        size_t operator()(const std::vector<T>& v) const {\n            size_t seed = 0;\n            for (const auto& i : v) {\n                seed ^= std::hash<T>{}(i)  + 0x9e3779b9 + (seed<<6) + (seed>>2);\n            }\n            return seed;\n        }\n    };\n\npublic:\n    vector<int> beautifulPair(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {\n        static const int INF = numeric_limits<int>::max();\n        static const int MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT = (8 + 2) / 2;\n\n        vector<vector<int>> points;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(nums1); ++i) {\n            points.push_back({nums1[i], nums2[i]});\n        }\n        vector<int> result(3, INF);\n        unordered_map<vector<int>, int, VectorHash<int>> lookup;\n        for (int i = size(points) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {\n            if (lookup.count(points[i])) {\n                result = min(result, vector<int>{0, i, lookup[points[i]]});\n            }\n            lookup[points[i]] = i;\n        }\n        if (result[0] == 0) {\n            return {result[1], result[2]};\n        }\n        vector<int> order(size(points));\n        iota(begin(order), end(order), 0);\n        sort(begin(order), end(order), [&](const auto& a, const auto& b) {\n            return points[a][0] < points[b][0];\n        });\n        const auto& dist = [&](auto a, auto b) {\n            if (a > b) {\n                swap(a, b);\n            }\n            return vector<int>{abs(points[a][0] - points[b][0]) + abs(points[a][1] - points[b][1]), a, b};\n        };\n\n        const function<void (int, int)> merge_sort = [&](int left, int right) {\n            const auto& update = [&](const auto& arr, int i) {  // added\n                for (int j = size(arr) - 1; j >= 0; --j) {\n                    if (points[i][1] - points[arr[j]][1] > result[0]) {\n                        break;\n                    }\n                    assert((size(arr) - 1) - j + 1 <= MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT);\n                    result = min(result, dist(i, arr[j]));\n                }\n            };\n            \n            if (left == right) {\n                return;\n            }\n            const int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;\n            const int x = points[order[mid]][0];  // added\n            merge_sort(left, mid);\n            merge_sort(mid + 1, right);\n            vector<int> tmp, tmp_l, tmp_r;\n            for (int l = left, r = mid + 1; l < mid + 1 || r < right + 1;) {\n                if (r >= right + 1 || (l < mid + 1 && points[order[l]][1] <= points[order[r]][1])) {  // modified\n                    update(tmp_r, order[l]);\n                    if (x - points[order[l]][0] <= result[0]) {  // added\n                        tmp_l.emplace_back(order[l]);\n                    }\n                    tmp.emplace_back(order[l++]);\n                } else {\n                    update(tmp_l, order[r]);\n                    if (points[order[r]][0] - x <= result[0]) {  // added\n                        tmp_r.emplace_back(order[r]);\n                    }\n                    tmp.emplace_back(order[r++]);\n                }\n            }\n            copy(cbegin(tmp), cend(tmp), begin(order) + left);\n        };\n        \n        merge_sort(0, size(points) - 1);\n        return {result[1], result[2]};\n    }\n};\n\n// Time:  O(nlogn)\n// Space: O(n)\n// divide and conquer, merge sort, variant of closest pair\n// reference: https://www.baeldung.com/cs/minimal-manhattan-distance\nclass Solution3 {\nprivate:\n    template<typename T>\n    struct VectorHash {\n        size_t operator()(const std::vector<T>& v) const {\n            size_t seed = 0;\n            for (const auto& i : v) {\n                seed ^= std::hash<T>{}(i)  + 0x9e3779b9 + (seed<<6) + (seed>>2);\n            }\n            return seed;\n        }\n    };\n\npublic:\n    vector<int> beautifulPair(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {\n        static const int INF = numeric_limits<int>::max();\n        static const int MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT = 8;\n\n        vector<vector<int>> points;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(nums1); ++i) {\n            points.push_back({nums1[i], nums2[i]});\n        }\n        vector<int> result(3, INF);\n        unordered_map<vector<int>, int, VectorHash<int>> lookup;\n        for (int i = size(points) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {\n            if (lookup.count(points[i])) {\n                result = min(result, vector<int>{0, i, lookup[points[i]]});\n            }\n            lookup[points[i]] = i;\n        }\n        if (result[0] == 0) {\n            return {result[1], result[2]};\n        }\n        vector<int> order(size(points));\n        iota(begin(order), end(order), 0);\n        sort(begin(order), end(order), [&](const auto& a, const auto& b) {\n            return points[a][0] < points[b][0];\n        });\n        const auto& dist = [&](auto a, auto b) {\n            if (a > b) {\n                swap(a, b);\n            }\n            return vector<int>{abs(points[a][0] - points[b][0]) + abs(points[a][1] - points[b][1]), a, b};\n        };\n\n        const function<void (int, int)> merge_sort = [&](int left, int right) {\n            if (left == right) {\n                return;\n            }\n            const int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;\n            const int x = points[order[mid]][0];  // added\n            merge_sort(left, mid);\n            merge_sort(mid + 1, right);\n            vector<int> tmp;\n            for (int l = left, r = mid + 1; l <= mid; ++l) {\n                while (r <= right && points[order[r]][1] < points[order[l]][1]) {  // modified\n                    tmp.emplace_back(order[r++]);\n                }\n                tmp.emplace_back(order[l]);\n            }\n            copy(cbegin(tmp), cend(tmp), begin(order) + left);\n\n            // added below\n            vector<int> stripe;\n            for (int i = left; i <= right; ++i) {\n                if (abs(points[order[i]][0] - x) <= result[0]) {\n                    stripe.emplace_back(order[i]);\n                }\n            }\n            for (int i = 0; i + 1 < size(stripe); ++i) {\n                for (int j = i + 1; j < size(stripe); ++j) {\n                    int x = stripe[i], y = stripe[j];\n                    if (points[y][1] - points[x][1] > result[0]) {\n                        break;\n                    }\n                    assert(j - (i + 1) + 1 <= MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT);\n                    result = min(result, dist(x, y));\n                }\n            }      \n        };\n        \n        merge_sort(0, size(points) - 1);\n        return {result[1], result[2]};\n    }\n};\n\n// Time:  O(nlogn)\n// Space: O(n)\n// segment tree\nclass Solution4 {\nprivate:\n    template<typename T>\n    struct VectorHash {\n        size_t operator()(const std::vector<T>& v) const {\n            size_t seed = 0;\n            for (const auto& i : v) {\n                seed ^= std::hash<T>{}(i)  + 0x9e3779b9 + (seed<<6) + (seed>>2);\n            }\n            return seed;\n        }\n    };\n\npublic:\n    vector<int> beautifulPair(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {\n        static const int INF = numeric_limits<int>::max();\n\n        vector<vector<int>> points;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(nums1); ++i) {\n            points.push_back({nums1[i], nums2[i]});\n        }\n        vector<int> result(3, INF);\n        unordered_map<vector<int>, int, VectorHash<int>> lookup;\n        for (int i = size(points) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {\n            if (lookup.count(points[i])) {\n                result = min(result, vector<int>{0, i, lookup[points[i]]});\n            }\n            lookup[points[i]] = i;\n        }\n        if (result[0] == 0) {\n            return {result[1], result[2]};\n        }\n        vector<int> order(size(points));\n        iota(begin(order), end(order), 0);\n        sort(begin(order), end(order), [&](const auto& a, const auto& b) {\n            return points[a][0] < points[b][0];\n        });\n        const auto& dist = [&](auto a, auto b) {\n            if (a > b) {\n                swap(a, b);\n            }\n            return vector<int>{abs(points[a][0] - points[b][0]) + abs(points[a][1] - points[b][1]), a, b};\n        };\n\n        unordered_set<int> y_set;\n        for (const auto& p : points) {\n            y_set.emplace(p[1]);\n        }\n        vector<int> sorted_y(cbegin(y_set), cend(y_set));\n        sort(begin(sorted_y), end(sorted_y));\n        unordered_map<int, int> y_to_idx;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(sorted_y); ++i) {  // coordinate compression\n            y_to_idx[sorted_y[i]] = i;\n        }\n        SegmentTree st1(size(y_to_idx)), st2(size(y_to_idx));\n        for (const auto& i : order) {\n            int j = -st1.query(0, y_to_idx[points[i][1]] - 1)[1];  // min((xi-xj)+(yi-yj) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1])) = (xi+yi)-max((xj+yj) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1]))\n            if (j != INF) {\n                assert(points[j][1] < points[i][1]);\n                result = min(result, dist(i, j));\n            }\n            st1.update(y_to_idx[points[i][1]], vector<int>{points[i][0] + points[i][1], -i});\n            j = -st2.query(y_to_idx[points[i][1]], size(y_to_idx) - 1)[1];   // min((xi-xj)+(yj-yi) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1], len(y_to_idx))) = (xi-yi)-max((xj-yj) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1], len(y_to_idx))\n            if (j != INF) {\n                assert(points[j][1] >= points[i][1]);\n                result = min(result, dist(i, j));\n            }\n            st2.update(y_to_idx[points[i][1]], vector<int>{points[i][0] - points[i][1], -i});\n        }\n        return {result[1], result[2]};\n    }\n\nprivate:\n    class SegmentTree {\n    private:\n        static const int INF = numeric_limits<int>::max();\n      \n    public:\n        explicit SegmentTree(int N)\n          : tree(N > 1 ? 1 << (__lg(N - 1) + 2) : 2, vector<int>{-INF, -INF}),\n            base(N > 1 ? 1 << (__lg(N - 1) + 1) : 1) {\n\n        }\n\n        void update(int i, const vector<int>& h) {\n            int x = base + i;\n            tree[x] = h;\n            while (x > 1) {\n                x /= 2;\n                tree[x] = max(tree[x * 2], tree[x * 2 + 1]);\n            }\n        }\n\n        vector<int> query(int L, int R) {\n            vector<int> result = {-INF, -INF};\n            if (L > R) {\n                return result;\n            }\n            L += base;\n            R += base;\n            for (; L <= R; L /= 2, R /= 2) {\n                if (L & 1) {\n                    result = max(result, tree[L]);\n                    ++L;\n                }\n                if ((R & 1) == 0) {\n                    result = max(tree[R], result);\n                    --R;\n                }\n            }\n            return result;\n        }\n\n        vector<vector<int>> tree;\n        int base;\n    };\n};\n20:T26a6,# Time:  O(n) on average\n# Space: O(n)\n\nimport random\nimport itertools\nimport math\n\n\n# random algorithms, variant of closest pair\n# reference: https://github.com/jilljenn/tryalgo/blob/master/tryalgo/closest_points.py\nrandom.seed(0)\nclass Solution(object):\n    def beautifulPair(self, nums1, nums2):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums1: List[int]\n        :type nums2: List[int]\n        :rtype: List[int]\n        \"\"\"\n        INF = float(\"inf\")\n        def dist(a, b):\n            if a[2] > b[2]:\n                a, b = b, a\n            return [abs(a[0]-b[0])+abs(a[1]-b[1]), a[2], b[2]]\n\n        def cell(point, size):\n            x, y, _ = point\n            return math.floor(x/size), math.floor(y/size)\n\n        def improve():\n            lookup = {}\n            for p in points:\n                i, j = map(int, cell(p, result[0]/2.0))\n                for ni in xrange(i-2, (i+2)+1):\n                    for nj in xrange(j-2, (j+2)+1):\n                        if (ni, nj) not in lookup:\n                            continue\n                        d = dist(p, lookup[ni, nj])\n                        if d < result:\n                            result[:] = d\n                            return True\n                lookup[i, j] = p\n            return False\n\n        points = [(i, j, idx) for idx, (i, j) in enumerate(itertools.izip(nums1, nums2))]\n        result = [INF]*3\n        lookup = {}\n        for i in reversed(xrange(len(points))):\n            if points[i][:2] in lookup:\n                result = [0, i, lookup[points[i][:2]]]\n            lookup[points[i][:2]] = i\n        if result[0] == 0:\n            return result[1:]\n        random.shuffle(points)\n        result = dist(points[0], points[1])\n        while improve():\n            pass\n        return result[1:]\n\n\n# Time:  O(nlogn)\n# Space: O(n)\nimport itertools\n\n\n# divide and conquer, merge sort, variant of closest pair\n# reference: https://www.baeldung.com/cs/minimal-manhattan-distance\nclass Solution2(object):\n    def beautifulPair(self, nums1, nums2):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums1: List[int]\n        :type nums2: List[int]\n        :rtype: List[int]\n        \"\"\"\n        INF = float(\"inf\")\n        MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT = (8+2)//2\n        def dist(a, b):\n            if a > b:\n                a, b = b, a\n            return [abs(points[a][0]-points[b][0])+abs(points[a][1]-points[b][1]), a, b]\n\n        def merge_sort(left, right):\n            def update(arr, i):  # added\n                for j in reversed(xrange(len(arr))):\n                    if points[i][1]-points[arr[j]][1] > result[0]:\n                        break\n                    result[:] = min(result, dist(i, arr[j]))\n                else:\n                    j = -1\n                assert((len(arr)-1)-j <= MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT)\n\n            if left == right:\n                return\n            mid = left+(right-left)//2\n            x = points[order[mid]][0]  # added\n            merge_sort(left, mid)\n            merge_sort(mid+1, right)\n            tmp, tmp_l, tmp_r = [], [], []\n            l, r = left, mid+1\n            while l <= mid or r <= right:\n                if r == right+1 or (l <= mid and points[order[l]][1] <= points[order[r]][1]):  # modified\n                    update(tmp_r, order[l])\n                    if x-points[order[l]][0] <= result[0]:  # added\n                        tmp_l.append(order[l])\n                    tmp.append(order[l])\n                    l += 1\n                else:\n                    update(tmp_l, order[r])\n                    if points[order[r]][0]-x <= result[0]:  # added\n                        tmp_r.append(order[r])\n                    tmp.append(order[r])\n                    r += 1\n            order[left:right+1] = tmp\n\n        points = [(i, j) for i, j in itertools.izip(nums1, nums2)]\n        result = [INF]*3\n        lookup = {}\n        for i in reversed(xrange(len(points))):\n            if points[i] in lookup:\n                result = [0, (i, lookup[points[i]])]\n            lookup[points[i]] = i\n        if result[0] == 0:\n            return result[1]\n        order = range(len(points))\n        order.sort(key=lambda x: points[x][0])\n        merge_sort(0, len(points)-1)\n        return result[1:]\n\n\n# Time:  O(nlogn)\n# Space: O(n)\nimport itertools\n\n\n# divide and conquer, merge sort, variant of closest pair\n# reference: https://www.baeldung.com/cs/minimal-manhattan-distance\nclass Solution3(object):\n    def beautifulPair(self, nums1, nums2):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums1: List[int]\n        :type nums2: List[int]\n        :rtype: List[int]\n        \"\"\"\n        INF = float(\"inf\")\n        MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT = 8\n        def dist(a, b):\n            if a > b:\n                a, b = b, a\n            return [abs(points[a][0]-points[b][0])+abs(points[a][1]-points[b][1]), a, b]\n\n        def merge_sort(left, right):\n            if left == right:\n                return\n            mid = left + (right-left)//2\n            x = points[order[mid]][0]  # added\n            merge_sort(left, mid)\n            merge_sort(mid+1, right)\n            r = mid+1\n            tmp = []\n            for l in xrange(left, mid+1):\n                while r <= right and points[order[r]][1] < points[order[l]][1]:  # modified\n                    tmp.append(order[r])\n                    r += 1\n                tmp.append(order[l])\n            order[left:left+len(tmp)] = tmp\n\n            # added below\n            stripe = [order[i] for i in xrange(left, right+1) if abs(points[order[i]][0]-x) <= result[0]]\n            for i in xrange(len(stripe)-1):\n                for j in xrange(i+1, len(stripe)):\n                    x, y = stripe[i], stripe[j]\n                    if points[y][1]-points[x][1] > result[0]:\n                        break\n                    result[:] = min(result, dist(x, y))\n                else:\n                    j = len(stripe)\n                assert(j-(i+1) <= MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT)\n\n        points = [(i, j) for i, j in itertools.izip(nums1, nums2)]\n        result = [INF]*3\n        lookup = {}\n        for i in reversed(xrange(len(points))):\n            if points[i] in lookup:\n                result = [0, (i, lookup[points[i]])]\n            lookup[points[i]] = i\n        if result[0] == 0:\n            return result[1]\n        order = range(len(points))\n        order.sort(key=lambda x: points[x][0])\n        merge_sort(0, len(points)-1)\n        return result[1:]\n\n\n# Time:  O(nlogn)\n# Space: O(n)\nimport itertools\n\n\n# segment tree\nclass Solution4(object):\n    def beautifulPair(self, nums1, nums2):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums1: List[int]\n        :type nums2: List[int]\n        :rtype: List[int]\n        \"\"\"\n        INF = float(\"inf\")\n        # Range Maximum Query\n        class SegmentTree(object):\n            def __init__(self, N,\n                         build_fn=lambda _: [-INF, -INF],  # modified\n                         query_fn=lambda x, y: y if x is None else x if y is None else max(x, y),\n                         update_fn=lambda x: x):\n                self.tree = [None]*(2*2**((N-1).bit_length()))\n                self.base = len(self.tree)//2\n                self.query_fn = query_fn\n                self.update_fn = update_fn\n                for i in xrange(self.base, self.base+N):\n                    self.tree[i] = build_fn(i-self.base)\n                for i in reversed(xrange(1, self.base)):\n                    self.tree[i] = query_fn(self.tree[2*i], self.tree[2*i+1])\n\n            def update(self, i, h):\n                x = self.base+i\n                self.tree[x] = self.update_fn(h)\n                while x > 1:\n                    x //= 2\n                    self.tree[x] = self.query_fn(self.tree[x*2], self.tree[x*2+1])\n\n            def query(self, L, R):\n                if L > R:\n                    return [-INF, -INF]  # modified\n                L += self.base\n                R += self.base\n                left = right = None\n                while L <= R:\n                    if L & 1:\n                        left = self.query_fn(left, self.tree[L])\n                        L += 1\n                    if R & 1 == 0:\n                        right = self.query_fn(self.tree[R], right)\n                        R -= 1\n                    L //= 2\n                    R //= 2\n                return self.query_fn(left, right)\n\n        def dist(a, b):\n            if a > b:\n                a, b = b, a\n            return [abs(points[a][0]-points[b][0])+abs(points[a][1]-points[b][1]), a, b]\n\n        points = [(i, j) for i, j in itertools.izip(nums1, nums2)]\n        result = [INF]*3\n        lookup = {}\n        for i in reversed(xrange(len(points))):\n            if points[i] in lookup:\n                result = [0, (i, lookup[points[i]])]\n            lookup[points[i]] = i\n        if result[0] == 0:\n            return result[1]\n        order = range(len(points))\n        order.sort(key=lambda x: points[x][0])\n        y_set = set(y for _, y in points)\n        y_to_idx = {y:i for i, y in enumerate(sorted(y_set))}\n        st1, st2 = SegmentTree(len(y_to_idx)), SegmentTree(len(y_to_idx))\n        for i in order:\n            j = -st1.query(0, y_to_idx[points[i][1]]-1)[1]  # min((xi-xj)+(yi-yj) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1])) = (xi+yi)-max((xj+yj) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1]))\n            if j != INF:\n                assert(points[j][1] < points[i][1])\n                result = min(result, dist(i, j))\n            st1.update(y_to_idx[points[i][1]], [points[i][0]+points[i][1], -i])\n            j = -st2.query(y_to_idx[points[i][1]], len(y_to_idx)-1)[1]  # min((xi-xj)+(yj-yi) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1], len(y_to_idx))) = (xi-yi)-max((xj-yj) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1], len(y_to_idx))\n            if j != INF:\n                assert(points[j][1] >= points[i][1])\n                result = min(result, dist(i, j))\n            st2.update(y_to_idx[points[i][1]], [points[i][0]-points[i][1], -i])\n        return result[1:]\n15:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"container-af py-10\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"nav\",null,{\"aria-label\":\"Breadcrumb\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Problems\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Beautiful Pairs\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/beautiful-pairs\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":4,\\\"name\\\":\\\"C++\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/beautiful-pairs/cpp\\\"}]}\"}}],[\"$\",\"ol\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",\"/\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[false,[\"$\",\"$L3\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"className\":\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\",\"children\":\"Home\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/problems\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"aria-hidden\":true,\"className\":\"text-border\",\"children\":\"/\"}],[\"$\",\"$L3\",null,{\"href\":\"/problems\",\"className\":\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\",\"children\":\"Problems\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/problems/beautiful-pairs\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"aria-hidden\":true,\"className\":\"text-border\",\"children\":\"/\"}],[\"$\",\"$L3\",null,{\"href\":\"/problems/beautiful-pairs\",\"className\":\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\",\"children\":\"Beautiful Pairs\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/problems/beautiful-pairs/cpp\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"aria-hidden\":true,\"className\":\"text-border\",\"children\":\"/\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground font-medium\",\"aria-current\":\"page\",\"children\":\"C++\"}]]}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-4 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-hard/15 text-hard\",\"children\":\"Hard\"}]}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight\",\"children\":[\"Beautiful Pairs\",\" — \",\"C++\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-2 text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L3\",null,{\"href\":\"/problems/beautiful-pairs\",\"className\":\"text-primary hover:underline\",\"children\":\"Full explanation\"}],\" · \",\"Time \",\"O(n) on average\",\" · Space \",\"O(n)\"]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-8\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L1e\",null,{\"solutions\":{\"cpp\":{\"language\":\"C++\",\"languageSlug\":\"cpp\",\"filename\":\"beautiful-pairs.cpp\",\"code\":\"$1f\",\"sourcePath\":\"C++/beautiful-pairs.cpp\"},\"python\":{\"language\":\"Python\",\"languageSlug\":\"python\",\"filename\":\"beautiful-pairs.py\",\"code\":\"$20\",\"sourcePath\":\"Python/beautiful-pairs.py\"}},\"defaultLang\":\"cpp\"}]}]]}]\n1b:[[\"$\",\"meta\",\"0\",{\"charSet\":\"utf-8\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"1\",{\"name\":\"viewport\",\"content\":\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\"}]]\n21:I[27201,[\"/_next/static/chunks/2fvm6eoqeukxu.js\",\"/_next/static/chunks/1ntn7efqc-iiw.js\",\"/_next/static/chunks/0plpm2axnqe9k.js\"],\"IconMark\"]\n18:null\n1d:[[\"$\",\"title\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Beautiful Pairs C++ Solution | AlgoForge\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"1\",{\"name\":\"description\",\"content\":\"C++ solution for Beautiful Pairs (LeetCode #2613). Time O(n) on average, space O(n).\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"2\",{\"name\":\"keywords\",\"content\":\"Beautiful Pairs cpp,Beautiful Pairs C++,cpp leetcode\"}],[\"$\",\"link\",\"3\",{\"rel\":\"canonical\",\"href\":\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/beautiful-pairs/cpp\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"4\",{\"property\":\"og:title\",\"content\":\"Beautiful Pairs C++ Solution | AlgoForge\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"5\",{\"property\":\"og:description\",\"content\":\"C++ solution for Beautiful Pairs (LeetCode #2613). Time O(n) on average, space O(n).\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"6\",{\"property\":\"og:url\",\"content\":\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/beautiful-pairs/cpp\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"7\",{\"property\":\"og:site_name\",\"content\":\"AlgoForge\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"8\",{\"property\":\"og:image\",\"content\":\"https://algoforge.dev/og-default.png\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"9\",{\"property\":\"og:image:width\",\"content\":\"1200\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"10\",{\"property\":\"og:image:height\",\"content\":\"630\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"11\",{\"property\":\"og:image:alt\",\"content\":\"Beautiful Pairs C++ Solution | AlgoForge\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"12\",{\"property\":\"og:type\",\"content\":\"article\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"13\",{\"name\":\"twitter:card\",\"content\":\"summary_large_image\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"14\",{\"name\":\"twitter:title\",\"content\":\"Beautiful Pairs C++ Solution | AlgoForge\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"15\",{\"name\":\"twitter:description\",\"content\":\"C++ solution for Beautiful Pairs (LeetCode #2613). Time O(n) on average, space O(n).\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"16\",{\"name\":\"twitter:image\",\"content\":\"https://algoforge.dev/og-default.png\"}],[\"$\",\"link\",\"17\",{\"rel\":\"icon\",\"href\":\"/favicon.ico?favicon.2vob68tjqpejf.ico\",\"sizes\":\"256x256\",\"type\":\"image/x-icon\"}],[\"$\",\"link\",\"18\",{\"rel\":\"icon\",\"href\":\"/favicon.ico\"}],[\"$\",\"$L21\",\"19\",{}]]\n","/problems/$d$slug/$d$lang/__PAGE__":"1:\"$Sreact.fragment\"\n2:I[522016,[\"/_next/static/chunks/2fvm6eoqeukxu.js\",\"/_next/static/chunks/1ntn7efqc-iiw.js\",\"/_next/static/chunks/0plpm2axnqe9k.js\",\"/_next/static/chunks/0a2gmow1_jiq0.js\"],\"\"]\n3:I[705747,[\"/_next/static/chunks/2fvm6eoqeukxu.js\",\"/_next/static/chunks/1ntn7efqc-iiw.js\",\"/_next/static/chunks/0plpm2axnqe9k.js\",\"/_next/static/chunks/0a2gmow1_jiq0.js\"],\"CodeTabs\"]\n8:I[897367,[\"/_next/static/chunks/2fvm6eoqeukxu.js\",\"/_next/static/chunks/1ntn7efqc-iiw.js\",\"/_next/static/chunks/0plpm2axnqe9k.js\"],\"OutletBoundary\"]\n9:\"$Sreact.suspense\"\n4:T356a,// Time:  O(n) on average\n// Space: O(n)\n\n// random algorithms, variant of closest pair\n// reference: https://github.com/jilljenn/tryalgo/blob/master/tryalgo/closest_points.py\nclass Solution {\nprivate:\n    template<typename T>\n    struct VectorHash {\n        size_t operator()(const std::vector<T>& v) const {\n            size_t seed = 0;\n            for (const auto& i : v) {\n                seed ^= std::hash<T>{}(i)  + 0x9e3779b9 + (seed<<6) + (seed>>2);\n            }\n            return seed;\n        }\n    };\n\npublic:\n    vector<int> beautifulPair(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {\n        static const int INF = numeric_limits<int>::max();\n        srand(time(0));\n\n        vector<vector<int>> points;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(nums1); ++i) {\n            points.push_back({nums1[i], nums2[i], i});\n        }\n        vector<int> result(3, INF);\n        unordered_map<vector<int>, int, VectorHash<int>> lookup;\n        for (int i = size(points) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {\n            const auto& key = vector<int>{points[i][0], points[i][1]};\n            if (lookup.count(key)) {\n                result = min(result, vector<int>{0, i, lookup[key]});\n            }\n            lookup[key] = i;\n        }\n        if (result[0] == 0) {\n            return {result[1], result[2]};\n        }\n        vector<int> order(size(points));\n        iota(begin(order), end(order), 0);\n        sort(begin(order), end(order), [&](const auto& a, const auto& b) {\n            return points[a] < points[b];\n        });\n        const auto& dist = [&](auto a, auto b) {\n            if (a[2] > b[2]) {\n                swap(a, b);\n            }\n            return vector<int>{abs(a[0] - b[0]) + abs(a[1] - b[1]), a[2], b[2]};\n        };\n\n        const auto& improve = [&]() {\n            unordered_map<vector<int>, vector<int>, VectorHash<int>> lookup;\n            for (const auto& p : points) {\n                const double size = result[0] / 2.0;\n                const int i = floor(p[0] / size), j = floor(p[1] / size);\n                for (int ni = i - 2; ni <= i + 2; ++ni) {\n                    for (int nj = j - 2; nj <= j + 2; ++nj) {\n                        const auto& key = vector<int>{ni, nj};\n                        if (!lookup.count(key)) {\n                            continue;\n                        }\n                        const auto& d = dist(p, lookup[key]);\n                        if (d < result) {\n                            result = d;\n                            return true;\n                        }\n                    }\n                }\n                lookup[vector<int>{i, j}] = p;\n            }\n            return false;\n        };\n\n        random_shuffle(begin(points), end(points));\n        result = dist(points[0], points[1]);\n        while (improve());\n        return {result[1], result[2]};\n    }\n};\n\n// Time:  O(nlogn)\n// Space: O(n)\n// divide and conquer, merge sort, variant of closest pair\n// reference: https://www.baeldung.com/cs/minimal-manhattan-distance\nclass Solution2 {\nprivate:\n    template<typename T>\n    struct VectorHash {\n        size_t operator()(const std::vector<T>& v) const {\n            size_t seed = 0;\n            for (const auto& i : v) {\n                seed ^= std::hash<T>{}(i)  + 0x9e3779b9 + (seed<<6) + (seed>>2);\n            }\n            return seed;\n        }\n    };\n\npublic:\n    vector<int> beautifulPair(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {\n        static const int INF = numeric_limits<int>::max();\n        static const int MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT = (8 + 2) / 2;\n\n        vector<vector<int>> points;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(nums1); ++i) {\n            points.push_back({nums1[i], nums2[i]});\n        }\n        vector<int> result(3, INF);\n        unordered_map<vector<int>, int, VectorHash<int>> lookup;\n        for (int i = size(points) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {\n            if (lookup.count(points[i])) {\n                result = min(result, vector<int>{0, i, lookup[points[i]]});\n            }\n            lookup[points[i]] = i;\n        }\n        if (result[0] == 0) {\n            return {result[1], result[2]};\n        }\n        vector<int> order(size(points));\n        iota(begin(order), end(order), 0);\n        sort(begin(order), end(order), [&](const auto& a, const auto& b) {\n            return points[a][0] < points[b][0];\n        });\n        const auto& dist = [&](auto a, auto b) {\n            if (a > b) {\n                swap(a, b);\n            }\n            return vector<int>{abs(points[a][0] - points[b][0]) + abs(points[a][1] - points[b][1]), a, b};\n        };\n\n        const function<void (int, int)> merge_sort = [&](int left, int right) {\n            const auto& update = [&](const auto& arr, int i) {  // added\n                for (int j = size(arr) - 1; j >= 0; --j) {\n                    if (points[i][1] - points[arr[j]][1] > result[0]) {\n                        break;\n                    }\n                    assert((size(arr) - 1) - j + 1 <= MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT);\n                    result = min(result, dist(i, arr[j]));\n                }\n            };\n            \n            if (left == right) {\n                return;\n            }\n            const int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;\n            const int x = points[order[mid]][0];  // added\n            merge_sort(left, mid);\n            merge_sort(mid + 1, right);\n            vector<int> tmp, tmp_l, tmp_r;\n            for (int l = left, r = mid + 1; l < mid + 1 || r < right + 1;) {\n                if (r >= right + 1 || (l < mid + 1 && points[order[l]][1] <= points[order[r]][1])) {  // modified\n                    update(tmp_r, order[l]);\n                    if (x - points[order[l]][0] <= result[0]) {  // added\n                        tmp_l.emplace_back(order[l]);\n                    }\n                    tmp.emplace_back(order[l++]);\n                } else {\n                    update(tmp_l, order[r]);\n                    if (points[order[r]][0] - x <= result[0]) {  // added\n                        tmp_r.emplace_back(order[r]);\n                    }\n                    tmp.emplace_back(order[r++]);\n                }\n            }\n            copy(cbegin(tmp), cend(tmp), begin(order) + left);\n        };\n        \n        merge_sort(0, size(points) - 1);\n        return {result[1], result[2]};\n    }\n};\n\n// Time:  O(nlogn)\n// Space: O(n)\n// divide and conquer, merge sort, variant of closest pair\n// reference: https://www.baeldung.com/cs/minimal-manhattan-distance\nclass Solution3 {\nprivate:\n    template<typename T>\n    struct VectorHash {\n        size_t operator()(const std::vector<T>& v) const {\n            size_t seed = 0;\n            for (const auto& i : v) {\n                seed ^= std::hash<T>{}(i)  + 0x9e3779b9 + (seed<<6) + (seed>>2);\n            }\n            return seed;\n        }\n    };\n\npublic:\n    vector<int> beautifulPair(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {\n        static const int INF = numeric_limits<int>::max();\n        static const int MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT = 8;\n\n        vector<vector<int>> points;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(nums1); ++i) {\n            points.push_back({nums1[i], nums2[i]});\n        }\n        vector<int> result(3, INF);\n        unordered_map<vector<int>, int, VectorHash<int>> lookup;\n        for (int i = size(points) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {\n            if (lookup.count(points[i])) {\n                result = min(result, vector<int>{0, i, lookup[points[i]]});\n            }\n            lookup[points[i]] = i;\n        }\n        if (result[0] == 0) {\n            return {result[1], result[2]};\n        }\n        vector<int> order(size(points));\n        iota(begin(order), end(order), 0);\n        sort(begin(order), end(order), [&](const auto& a, const auto& b) {\n            return points[a][0] < points[b][0];\n        });\n        const auto& dist = [&](auto a, auto b) {\n            if (a > b) {\n                swap(a, b);\n            }\n            return vector<int>{abs(points[a][0] - points[b][0]) + abs(points[a][1] - points[b][1]), a, b};\n        };\n\n        const function<void (int, int)> merge_sort = [&](int left, int right) {\n            if (left == right) {\n                return;\n            }\n            const int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;\n            const int x = points[order[mid]][0];  // added\n            merge_sort(left, mid);\n            merge_sort(mid + 1, right);\n            vector<int> tmp;\n            for (int l = left, r = mid + 1; l <= mid; ++l) {\n                while (r <= right && points[order[r]][1] < points[order[l]][1]) {  // modified\n                    tmp.emplace_back(order[r++]);\n                }\n                tmp.emplace_back(order[l]);\n            }\n            copy(cbegin(tmp), cend(tmp), begin(order) + left);\n\n            // added below\n            vector<int> stripe;\n            for (int i = left; i <= right; ++i) {\n                if (abs(points[order[i]][0] - x) <= result[0]) {\n                    stripe.emplace_back(order[i]);\n                }\n            }\n            for (int i = 0; i + 1 < size(stripe); ++i) {\n                for (int j = i + 1; j < size(stripe); ++j) {\n                    int x = stripe[i], y = stripe[j];\n                    if (points[y][1] - points[x][1] > result[0]) {\n                        break;\n                    }\n                    assert(j - (i + 1) + 1 <= MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT);\n                    result = min(result, dist(x, y));\n                }\n            }      \n        };\n        \n        merge_sort(0, size(points) - 1);\n        return {result[1], result[2]};\n    }\n};\n\n// Time:  O(nlogn)\n// Space: O(n)\n// segment tree\nclass Solution4 {\nprivate:\n    template<typename T>\n    struct VectorHash {\n        size_t operator()(const std::vector<T>& v) const {\n            size_t seed = 0;\n            for (const auto& i : v) {\n                seed ^= std::hash<T>{}(i)  + 0x9e3779b9 + (seed<<6) + (seed>>2);\n            }\n            return seed;\n        }\n    };\n\npublic:\n    vector<int> beautifulPair(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {\n        static const int INF = numeric_limits<int>::max();\n\n        vector<vector<int>> points;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(nums1); ++i) {\n            points.push_back({nums1[i], nums2[i]});\n        }\n        vector<int> result(3, INF);\n        unordered_map<vector<int>, int, VectorHash<int>> lookup;\n        for (int i = size(points) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {\n            if (lookup.count(points[i])) {\n                result = min(result, vector<int>{0, i, lookup[points[i]]});\n            }\n            lookup[points[i]] = i;\n        }\n        if (result[0] == 0) {\n            return {result[1], result[2]};\n        }\n        vector<int> order(size(points));\n        iota(begin(order), end(order), 0);\n        sort(begin(order), end(order), [&](const auto& a, const auto& b) {\n            return points[a][0] < points[b][0];\n        });\n        const auto& dist = [&](auto a, auto b) {\n            if (a > b) {\n                swap(a, b);\n            }\n            return vector<int>{abs(points[a][0] - points[b][0]) + abs(points[a][1] - points[b][1]), a, b};\n        };\n\n        unordered_set<int> y_set;\n        for (const auto& p : points) {\n            y_set.emplace(p[1]);\n        }\n        vector<int> sorted_y(cbegin(y_set), cend(y_set));\n        sort(begin(sorted_y), end(sorted_y));\n        unordered_map<int, int> y_to_idx;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(sorted_y); ++i) {  // coordinate compression\n            y_to_idx[sorted_y[i]] = i;\n        }\n        SegmentTree st1(size(y_to_idx)), st2(size(y_to_idx));\n        for (const auto& i : order) {\n            int j = -st1.query(0, y_to_idx[points[i][1]] - 1)[1];  // min((xi-xj)+(yi-yj) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1])) = (xi+yi)-max((xj+yj) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1]))\n            if (j != INF) {\n                assert(points[j][1] < points[i][1]);\n                result = min(result, dist(i, j));\n            }\n            st1.update(y_to_idx[points[i][1]], vector<int>{points[i][0] + points[i][1], -i});\n            j = -st2.query(y_to_idx[points[i][1]], size(y_to_idx) - 1)[1];   // min((xi-xj)+(yj-yi) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1], len(y_to_idx))) = (xi-yi)-max((xj-yj) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1], len(y_to_idx))\n            if (j != INF) {\n                assert(points[j][1] >= points[i][1]);\n                result = min(result, dist(i, j));\n            }\n            st2.update(y_to_idx[points[i][1]], vector<int>{points[i][0] - points[i][1], -i});\n        }\n        return {result[1], result[2]};\n    }\n\nprivate:\n    class SegmentTree {\n    private:\n        static const int INF = numeric_limits<int>::max();\n      \n    public:\n        explicit SegmentTree(int N)\n          : tree(N > 1 ? 1 << (__lg(N - 1) + 2) : 2, vector<int>{-INF, -INF}),\n            base(N > 1 ? 1 << (__lg(N - 1) + 1) : 1) {\n\n        }\n\n        void update(int i, const vector<int>& h) {\n            int x = base + i;\n            tree[x] = h;\n            while (x > 1) {\n                x /= 2;\n                tree[x] = max(tree[x * 2], tree[x * 2 + 1]);\n            }\n        }\n\n        vector<int> query(int L, int R) {\n            vector<int> result = {-INF, -INF};\n            if (L > R) {\n                return result;\n            }\n            L += base;\n            R += base;\n            for (; L <= R; L /= 2, R /= 2) {\n                if (L & 1) {\n                    result = max(result, tree[L]);\n                    ++L;\n                }\n                if ((R & 1) == 0) {\n                    result = max(tree[R], result);\n                    --R;\n                }\n            }\n            return result;\n        }\n\n        vector<vector<int>> tree;\n        int base;\n    };\n};\n5:T26a6,# Time:  O(n) on average\n# Space: O(n)\n\nimport random\nimport itertools\nimport math\n\n\n# random algorithms, variant of closest pair\n# reference: https://github.com/jilljenn/tryalgo/blob/master/tryalgo/closest_points.py\nrandom.seed(0)\nclass Solution(object):\n    def beautifulPair(self, nums1, nums2):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums1: List[int]\n        :type nums2: List[int]\n        :rtype: List[int]\n        \"\"\"\n        INF = float(\"inf\")\n        def dist(a, b):\n            if a[2] > b[2]:\n                a, b = b, a\n            return [abs(a[0]-b[0])+abs(a[1]-b[1]), a[2], b[2]]\n\n        def cell(point, size):\n            x, y, _ = point\n            return math.floor(x/size), math.floor(y/size)\n\n        def improve():\n            lookup = {}\n            for p in points:\n                i, j = map(int, cell(p, result[0]/2.0))\n                for ni in xrange(i-2, (i+2)+1):\n                    for nj in xrange(j-2, (j+2)+1):\n                        if (ni, nj) not in lookup:\n                            continue\n                        d = dist(p, lookup[ni, nj])\n                        if d < result:\n                            result[:] = d\n                            return True\n                lookup[i, j] = p\n            return False\n\n        points = [(i, j, idx) for idx, (i, j) in enumerate(itertools.izip(nums1, nums2))]\n        result = [INF]*3\n        lookup = {}\n        for i in reversed(xrange(len(points))):\n            if points[i][:2] in lookup:\n                result = [0, i, lookup[points[i][:2]]]\n            lookup[points[i][:2]] = i\n        if result[0] == 0:\n            return result[1:]\n        random.shuffle(points)\n        result = dist(points[0], points[1])\n        while improve():\n            pass\n        return result[1:]\n\n\n# Time:  O(nlogn)\n# Space: O(n)\nimport itertools\n\n\n# divide and conquer, merge sort, variant of closest pair\n# reference: https://www.baeldung.com/cs/minimal-manhattan-distance\nclass Solution2(object):\n    def beautifulPair(self, nums1, nums2):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums1: List[int]\n        :type nums2: List[int]\n        :rtype: List[int]\n        \"\"\"\n        INF = float(\"inf\")\n        MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT = (8+2)//2\n        def dist(a, b):\n            if a > b:\n                a, b = b, a\n            return [abs(points[a][0]-points[b][0])+abs(points[a][1]-points[b][1]), a, b]\n\n        def merge_sort(left, right):\n            def update(arr, i):  # added\n                for j in reversed(xrange(len(arr))):\n                    if points[i][1]-points[arr[j]][1] > result[0]:\n                        break\n                    result[:] = min(result, dist(i, arr[j]))\n                else:\n                    j = -1\n                assert((len(arr)-1)-j <= MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT)\n\n            if left == right:\n                return\n            mid = left+(right-left)//2\n            x = points[order[mid]][0]  # added\n            merge_sort(left, mid)\n            merge_sort(mid+1, right)\n            tmp, tmp_l, tmp_r = [], [], []\n            l, r = left, mid+1\n            while l <= mid or r <= right:\n                if r == right+1 or (l <= mid and points[order[l]][1] <= points[order[r]][1]):  # modified\n                    update(tmp_r, order[l])\n                    if x-points[order[l]][0] <= result[0]:  # added\n                        tmp_l.append(order[l])\n                    tmp.append(order[l])\n                    l += 1\n                else:\n                    update(tmp_l, order[r])\n                    if points[order[r]][0]-x <= result[0]:  # added\n                        tmp_r.append(order[r])\n                    tmp.append(order[r])\n                    r += 1\n            order[left:right+1] = tmp\n\n        points = [(i, j) for i, j in itertools.izip(nums1, nums2)]\n        result = [INF]*3\n        lookup = {}\n        for i in reversed(xrange(len(points))):\n            if points[i] in lookup:\n                result = [0, (i, lookup[points[i]])]\n            lookup[points[i]] = i\n        if result[0] == 0:\n            return result[1]\n        order = range(len(points))\n        order.sort(key=lambda x: points[x][0])\n        merge_sort(0, len(points)-1)\n        return result[1:]\n\n\n# Time:  O(nlogn)\n# Space: O(n)\nimport itertools\n\n\n# divide and conquer, merge sort, variant of closest pair\n# reference: https://www.baeldung.com/cs/minimal-manhattan-distance\nclass Solution3(object):\n    def beautifulPair(self, nums1, nums2):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums1: List[int]\n        :type nums2: List[int]\n        :rtype: List[int]\n        \"\"\"\n        INF = float(\"inf\")\n        MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT = 8\n        def dist(a, b):\n            if a > b:\n                a, b = b, a\n            return [abs(points[a][0]-points[b][0])+abs(points[a][1]-points[b][1]), a, b]\n\n        def merge_sort(left, right):\n            if left == right:\n                return\n            mid = left + (right-left)//2\n            x = points[order[mid]][0]  # added\n            merge_sort(left, mid)\n            merge_sort(mid+1, right)\n            r = mid+1\n            tmp = []\n            for l in xrange(left, mid+1):\n                while r <= right and points[order[r]][1] < points[order[l]][1]:  # modified\n                    tmp.append(order[r])\n                    r += 1\n                tmp.append(order[l])\n            order[left:left+len(tmp)] = tmp\n\n            # added below\n            stripe = [order[i] for i in xrange(left, right+1) if abs(points[order[i]][0]-x) <= result[0]]\n            for i in xrange(len(stripe)-1):\n                for j in xrange(i+1, len(stripe)):\n                    x, y = stripe[i], stripe[j]\n                    if points[y][1]-points[x][1] > result[0]:\n                        break\n                    result[:] = min(result, dist(x, y))\n                else:\n                    j = len(stripe)\n                assert(j-(i+1) <= MAX_NEIGHBOR_COUNT)\n\n        points = [(i, j) for i, j in itertools.izip(nums1, nums2)]\n        result = [INF]*3\n        lookup = {}\n        for i in reversed(xrange(len(points))):\n            if points[i] in lookup:\n                result = [0, (i, lookup[points[i]])]\n            lookup[points[i]] = i\n        if result[0] == 0:\n            return result[1]\n        order = range(len(points))\n        order.sort(key=lambda x: points[x][0])\n        merge_sort(0, len(points)-1)\n        return result[1:]\n\n\n# Time:  O(nlogn)\n# Space: O(n)\nimport itertools\n\n\n# segment tree\nclass Solution4(object):\n    def beautifulPair(self, nums1, nums2):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums1: List[int]\n        :type nums2: List[int]\n        :rtype: List[int]\n        \"\"\"\n        INF = float(\"inf\")\n        # Range Maximum Query\n        class SegmentTree(object):\n            def __init__(self, N,\n                         build_fn=lambda _: [-INF, -INF],  # modified\n                         query_fn=lambda x, y: y if x is None else x if y is None else max(x, y),\n                         update_fn=lambda x: x):\n                self.tree = [None]*(2*2**((N-1).bit_length()))\n                self.base = len(self.tree)//2\n                self.query_fn = query_fn\n                self.update_fn = update_fn\n                for i in xrange(self.base, self.base+N):\n                    self.tree[i] = build_fn(i-self.base)\n                for i in reversed(xrange(1, self.base)):\n                    self.tree[i] = query_fn(self.tree[2*i], self.tree[2*i+1])\n\n            def update(self, i, h):\n                x = self.base+i\n                self.tree[x] = self.update_fn(h)\n                while x > 1:\n                    x //= 2\n                    self.tree[x] = self.query_fn(self.tree[x*2], self.tree[x*2+1])\n\n            def query(self, L, R):\n                if L > R:\n                    return [-INF, -INF]  # modified\n                L += self.base\n                R += self.base\n                left = right = None\n                while L <= R:\n                    if L & 1:\n                        left = self.query_fn(left, self.tree[L])\n                        L += 1\n                    if R & 1 == 0:\n                        right = self.query_fn(self.tree[R], right)\n                        R -= 1\n                    L //= 2\n                    R //= 2\n                return self.query_fn(left, right)\n\n        def dist(a, b):\n            if a > b:\n                a, b = b, a\n            return [abs(points[a][0]-points[b][0])+abs(points[a][1]-points[b][1]), a, b]\n\n        points = [(i, j) for i, j in itertools.izip(nums1, nums2)]\n        result = [INF]*3\n        lookup = {}\n        for i in reversed(xrange(len(points))):\n            if points[i] in lookup:\n                result = [0, (i, lookup[points[i]])]\n            lookup[points[i]] = i\n        if result[0] == 0:\n            return result[1]\n        order = range(len(points))\n        order.sort(key=lambda x: points[x][0])\n        y_set = set(y for _, y in points)\n        y_to_idx = {y:i for i, y in enumerate(sorted(y_set))}\n        st1, st2 = SegmentTree(len(y_to_idx)), SegmentTree(len(y_to_idx))\n        for i in order:\n            j = -st1.query(0, y_to_idx[points[i][1]]-1)[1]  # min((xi-xj)+(yi-yj) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1])) = (xi+yi)-max((xj+yj) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1]))\n            if j != INF:\n                assert(points[j][1] < points[i][1])\n                result = min(result, dist(i, j))\n            st1.update(y_to_idx[points[i][1]], [points[i][0]+points[i][1], -i])\n            j = -st2.query(y_to_idx[points[i][1]], len(y_to_idx)-1)[1]  # min((xi-xj)+(yj-yi) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1], len(y_to_idx))) = (xi-yi)-max((xj-yj) for j in range(y_to_idx[points[i][1], len(y_to_idx))\n            if j != INF:\n                assert(points[j][1] >= points[i][1])\n                result = min(result, dist(i, j))\n            st2.update(y_to_idx[points[i][1]], [points[i][0]-points[i][1], -i])\n        return result[1:]\n0:{\"rsc\":[\"$\",\"$1\",\"c\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"container-af py-10\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"nav\",null,{\"aria-label\":\"Breadcrumb\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Problems\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"htt